///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @addtogroup MIDILAR_Examples_MidiCore
 * @brief Examples demonstrating core MIDI functionality using the MidiCore module.
 *
 * This group gathers practical examples that explore core components of the `MidiCore` module,
 * including message construction, byte-level parsing, callback handling, and parser configuration.
 *
 * These examples serve as a reference for using MIDI communication efficiently in both desktop and
 * embedded environments, and help clarify how to structure MIDI workflows with the MIDILAR library.
 *
 * The examples are divided by functionality:
 * - Constructing and sending MIDI messages
 * - Parsing MIDI byte streams with standalone or instance-bound callbacks
 * - Simulating realistic MIDI input, including noise
 * - Real-time byte-by-byte parsing for serial interfaces (e.g., Arduino)
 *
 * Each example is self-contained and highlights best practices for robust MIDI handling.
 */
